    capsule: "Short, smelly, and covered completely by a heavy, hooded cloak. Mousey, even for a Jawa, Akkik has always had a reputation for being a nasty little piece of vermin. His exploits in and around Mos Eisley soon earned him the respect of one of Jabba's guards, who took it upon himself to propose that Akkik join the guards. Jabba agreed, and fired the proposing guard on the spot to make room for Akkik. Covetous, nasty, tricky, a coward, and talks a lot. Nobody can understand him (and Akkik is not his real name, anyway), but that doesn't bother him a bit. His objective is to work for Jabba as long as Jabba continues to feed him.",
