    forcePoints: 2,
    characterPoints: 10,
    move: 10,
    equipment: "700 credits (on hand), credit voucher, datapad, blaster pistol (4D damage)",
    capsule: "There are plenty of slime ball crime kings in the galaxy, but Oro Freatt is just a ball of slime. Small, oily, and officious — living proof that there are things more irritating than mouse droids. Always dressed in garish, tasteless clothing and flashing cash. He has transformed Shownar into a tourist trap and crime center, maintaining power through a well-run, highly disciplined organization of several thousand trained business people rather than hired thugs. Each criminal organization gets control of a specific industry (labor unions, food, transportation) while Freatt's organization takes a percentage and directly controls communications and energy. He owns all property on the planet, collecting massive rents. He bribes the Imperial governor, sheltering immense sums through underreporting and shadow transactions — but sends enough to keep the sector government happy ('Rest assured, my dear Moff, there is positively no treasonous activity on Shownar'). Local police overlook smuggling but handle violent criminals harshly. He is in serious trouble if the Empire ever moves in force, so he makes every effort to appear subservient and loyal.",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.36"
