    capsule: "Churhee's Riflemen, named after deceased founder Vlaydm Churhee, are an experienced scout company specializing in low-profile rear-guard harassment operations. Once a truly mercenary outfit changing sides for the highest bidder, they turned anti-Imperial after the Empire failed to provide backup on a mission in Y'Trella system — a disaster that killed Churhee himself. Now they only accept anti-Imperial contracts. The unit prides itself on marksmanship; all line squads are actually sharpshooter squads with 6D+ blaster skills. Currently operating at 65-70% strength in Sarin and Parmel Sectors. Their presence may force Moff Tallis to allocate additional Fleet resources to Battlegroup Operations on Turcan III — if so, the Alliance will need to evacuate ground forces from the Turcan system.",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.55"
