    equipment: "Heavy blaster pistol (5D damage); other equipment varies by mission — supplies scavenged from targets or hijacked from Imperial convoys",
    capsule: "The Laramus Base Irregulars are a small, ragged company of quasi-Rebel soldiers specializing in missions so dangerous that members are known as 'dead men.' Commanded by Tagg Pierce, a former Rebel lieutenant noted for utter contempt for line officers. Originally operated from Laramus Base in Parmic Sector until it was destroyed by Imperial reprisals. Now homeless and highly mobile, fragmented into sub-units of 2-4 squads spread across many systems. Structured as a heavy line company of six heavy infantry platoons and two heavy weapons platoons, with specialist skills rivalling a Rebel SpecForces unit. However, their discipline is so lax and commanders so disliked by Rebel Command that they are considered expendable — often sent into suicide missions to avoid wasting SpecForces. Despite this, they have an incredibly high success rate, though casualties can reach 95%.",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.56"
