    specialAbilities: "",
    forcePoints: 0,
    characterPoints: 0,
    move: 11,
    equipment: "Nova Guard armor (+1D head and torso physical and energy, -1D Dexterity and skills)",
    capsule: "The Nova Guard of the Ailon system have a reputation for martial prowess on par with the Imperial Royal Guard and the Mandalorians. For a Nova Guard, training for combat is an act of religious devotion, part of a martial tradition stretching back more than 13,000 years. Battle honors are so numerous that they are only fully displayed on the most prestigious ceremonial occasions — each Honors Platoon Guardsman carries a banner with up to 30 honors. The Ailon people are firm believers in survival of the fittest and regard the Empire and Emperor Palpatine as the most fit and strong force in existence, making them fiercely loyal — though the Empire has no great love for non-Humans. Under Imperial rule, their military activities have been reduced in favor of ceremonial duties. The annual Ailon Military Ceremonies are one of the most prestigious events in the military calendar, with Empire-wide coverage. The Emperor, recognizing that conquering Ailon would be costly, harnessed their warlike nature instead — occasionally using them as cannon fodder presented as 'a great battle that only the Nova Guard can perform.'",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.57-58"
