    capsule: "Grefnakk is a typical Gamorrean: crude and extremely dangerous. Likes nothing better than smashing in a few heads. Will sometimes work with another hunter to provide brains to his brawn, but equally willing to go it alone. Makes it a point to go after high-risk, big-reward bounties. A brute and bully who overlooks the Gamorrean tradition of contract by combat — simply accepts credits since 'the blood part will come soon enough.' An excellent urban street fighter who prefers brawling to 'puny' energy weapons. Loyal only to himself. In four years of hunting he has amassed 74 captures. Prior to bounty hunting, he was sold into slavery by his clan and served as a thug for the Maldor Ring of slavers near Ryloth, earning his freedom by saving the ring's second-in-command during a rival ambush.",
    source: "WEG40073 Galaxy Guide 10: Bounty Hunters p.76"
