    capsule: "Shirlee Faughn has been a friend and assistant to Samuel Gillespee since she was a teenager. A Corellian, she signed aboard the Kern's Pride as a communications apprentice and quickly learned both space communications and the smuggling trade. She is at heart a very serious woman who constantly analyzes her surroundings, almost never smiling or joking on duty — though off-duty she spins hilarious yarns in the galley. Faultlessly polite, she despises physical violence as uncultured, though she has been known to man a quad-mount and blow Imperial ships to pieces when justified. She is in her forties, slender with short dark hair and piercing black eyes, dressed in gray steelcloth trousers, a white tunic and a blue flight jacket.",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.101"
