    capsule: "Born into Coruscant privilege, son of Baron Admiral Ronnan Tyla Vedij. Career Imperial Navy officer whose advancement stalled when the Emperor began seeding New Order loyalists into command positions. After his parents were assassinated in a staged 'traffic accident' on Coruscant — likely ordered by the Emperor due to his father's vocal opposition to military reforms — Vedij and his younger brother Elon were transferred together to the Far Orbit, presumably to facilitate their 'removal.' When Captain Kenit's reckless assault on the Silent Blades pirate stronghold killed every Imperial pilot including Elon, Vedij's plans for mutiny crystallized. He seized the ship after Alderaan's destruction, ejected Kenit and loyalists in escape pods, and secured a Letter of Marque from the Rebel Alliance to privateer against Imperial shipping in the Core Worlds. An inscrutable, seemingly passionless individual whose quiet nature belies fiery determination. Excellent strategist and tactician with 7D melee combat and 7D martial arts.",
