    specialAbilities: "",
    forcePoints: 3,
    darkSidePoints: 4,
    characterPoints: 20,
    move: 11,
    equipment: "Blaster pistol (4D damage), comlink. Mission equipment: blaster rifle (5D), blaster pistol (4D), knife (STR+1D), five grenades (5D), demolitions kit, survival kit, macrobinoculars, comlink, rations, five medpacs, protective helmet and vest (+2 to STR)",
    capsule: "Qell Tepine is head of a mercenary army called Star's Nova and worked extensively for the Rebel Alliance during the days of the war with the Empire. Since that time, however, he has proven that his true love is money — he works for whoever will pay his price. Tepine is not only a mercenary but also a ruthless profiteer. Somehow he gained access to most of the New Republic's ground forces, battle codes, and encrypting methods, making him doubly dangerous as he knows the code phrases and procedures that would allow him to infiltrate Republic forces or access their bases. All available information suggests that Tepine has no particular dislike for the Republic, but simply that other forces have offered him more for his services. He is known to have worked for the Empire, the pirate Safonne Pendon, and the crime boss Jor Idrall. Cracken once worked with Tepine on a large-scale operation to sabotage the Empire's TIE Interceptor design and construction efforts on the industrial world of Lianna — they barely escaped with their lives but delayed the fighter's completion by several months. The most recent encounter was in the Farseen system, where a Star's Nova strike team penetrated a New Republic command center and sabotaged its perimeter defenses, allowing the base to be taken by the Empire. STAR'S NOVA ORGANIZATION: 600 soldiers plus 200 support personnel, drawn from former Imperial Special Missions and Alliance SpecForce teams. Elite rapid-deployment mercenary task force. Base personnel stats: DEX 3D+2 (blaster 5D+1, blaster artillery 5D+1, dodge 4D+2, melee combat 5D), KNO 2D+2 (survival 4D), MEC 2D+2 (beast riding 4D, repulsorlift operation 4D), PER 2D+1 (bargain 4D+1, con 4D+1, hide 3D+1, search 5D, sneak 3D+2), STR 3D+2 (climbing/jumping 5D, stamina 5D), TEC 3D (demolition 4D, first aid 4D, security 4D+2). Dark Side Points: 0-5. Character Points: 0-20. Equipment: blaster rifle (5D), four grenades (5D), blaster pistol (4D), survival kit, macrobinoculars, comlink, rations, five medpacs, protective vest (armor code +1). Specializations: Reconnaissance (recons/pathfinders — survival +2D, beast riding +1D+1, hide +2D+1, search +2D, sneak +2D, climbing/lifting +1D), Field Command (ficomms — streetwise +1D, repulsorlift operations +1D+2, command +2D, security +2D+1), Light Weapons (el-weps — blaster +2D, blaster artillery +1D, grenade +2D, vehicle blasters +1D, hide +2D, sneak +1D), Heavy Weapons (h-weps — blaster +1D, blaster artillery +2D, grenade +1D, missile weapons +2D, vehicle blasters +2D, starship gunnery +1D, hide +1D, sneak +1D), Medics (alien species +1D, planetary systems +1D+1, survival +1D, first aid +3D, medicine +2D), Intelligence (intspecs — alien species +2D, cultures +2D, languages +2D, planetary systems +2D, streetwise +1D, bargain +1D, con +1D), Communications/Electronics (coms — languages +2D, streetwise +1D, communications +2D, sensors +2D, hide +1D, sneak +1D, search +1D, blaster repair +1D+2, demolition +1D, computer programming/repair +1D, droid programming +1D, droid repair +1D, repulsorlift repair +1D, security +2D, space transports repair +1D, starfighter repair +1D), Demolitions (demspecs — blaster artillery +1D, grenade +1D, planetary systems +1D, hide +1D, search +1D, sneak +1D, computer programming/repair +1D, demolition +2D, security +1D).",
    source: "WEG40062 Wanted by Cracken pp.65-68"
