    forcePoints: 0,
    characterPoints: 0,
    move: 6,
    equipment: "Three wheeled legs, video sensor, fine manipulator arm (+1D repair skills), heavy duty arc welder (4D+1, range 0.5/1/1.5 meters, +1D repair skills), video display screen, portable nav storage unit (stores coordinates for one hyperspace jump), acoustic signaler, hold-out blaster (3D+2)",
    capsule: "R4-B11 appears to be a standard, beat-up agromech droid similar to R2 units, designed for farm machinery and vehicles. In reality, it's a cranky assassin droid modified by Slythor. The Squib crime lord tried B11 at every possible job — valet, pilot, guard, entertainment unit — but in frustration disassembled it and added modifications including an enhanced arc welder and concealed blaster. Slythor uses B11 as a trade item with his enemies: days after departing Korad, B11 betrays its new owners, neutralizes them, takes control of the ship, and plots a hyperspace jump back to Korad where the new prize is delivered to Slythor. As the Squib is fond of remarking, 'the best trade is for a free object.'",
    source: "WEG40132 Operation: Elrood p.32"
