    equipment: "Dancer's costume, make-up kit, personal jewelry",
    capsule: "A tall, lithe Devaronian with a dancer's grace, Brinaloy N'Vaari is the granddaughter of the late Provincial Governor N'Vaari of Le Yer on Abregado-rae. She uses performing as an escape from the stresses of being in the public spotlight. When her grandfather was ruthlessly murdered by A'jidre Skrigatov — leaving her the last living member of the family — she was not able to avoid the gangster's grasp. Skrigatov forced her into an engagement to cement his political power, but with his goons stretched thin trying to influence the voters, Brinaloy found a way to vanish. A skilled impersonator who studied acting for years, she can convincingly disguise herself as a Twi'lek, Elomin, or Human of either gender. She fled to Phyrstal Island where she performs at Njinska's Tavern as a female Twi'lek singer.",
