    equipment: "Governor-General's cloak, heavy blaster pistol (5D), scrambled comlink, macrobinoculars",
    capsule: "On most worlds, being a convicted criminal would hamper your pursuit of political office; not on Dalos IV. The fact that she served time for smuggling actually inspired her campaign slogan — 'At least I'm honest about being a crook' — and helped Lira win the post of Governor-General. While Dalos IV has only a small human population, Lira's sharp wit and vibrant personality have endeared her to the populace, and no one seems to care that she runs an openly corrupt government. The economy is good, tourism money flows freely, and Lira turned the trophy chase into a huge source of revenue for the planet. A former smuggler, Lira is deadly with a blaster and in good enough shape to beat most of her bodyguards. She maintains her old freighter 'just in case something tempting comes up.' She manages Jabba the Hutt's interests on Dalos IV in exchange for a cut of the gambling profits.",
