    capsule: "Little does Moff Jarnek know, but his loyal 'pet' is actually one of the Alliance's most deeply placed spies. Dælar vuv Tertarrnek is a Covallon — a quadrupedal species of somewhat bestial appearance that most humans assume are unintelligent. The Alliance arranged for him to be passed off as an animal and given to Moff Jarnek as a 'pet.' From the side of the ruler of Tandon sector, vuv Tertarrnek has learned much about troop and fleet movements, even obtaining top-priority access codes that allowed the Alliance to tap Imperial communications. He sends short coded bursts from a long-range tight-beam comlink hidden in the Moff's palace, relayed by a stealth-equipped probot in Spirador system. General Cracken notes that vuv Tertarrnek's success demonstrates how the Empire's narrow-minded treatment of aliens as lesser beings plays right into Alliance hands.",
