    capsule: "It was far from easy for ibn Garl to claw his way up the corporate ladder. He has had to sacrifice a lot to make it — including his morals and his ethics. One of the few Sullustans to earn a position of authority in Vaufthau, he successfully lobbied his superiors for the resources to acquire secondary exploitation rights on Goroth. Under his leadership, the Vaufthau operation is engaged in extensive industrial espionage targeting virtually all the other corporations on Goroth. He is secretive in the extreme, never letting his left hand know what his right is doing. His attitude: 'All's fair in love and war... and business is the highest form of war.'",
