    equipment: "Blaster pistol (4D), vibro-blade (STR+1D+2)",
    capsule: "Lens is an Alliance general and leader of the Roughnecks, a group of ~60 Irregular guerrillas based on 'Home,' a clunky old giant water hauler hidden in Fakir sector space. She is 55 standard years old, about 1.6 meters tall, and looks like a dumpy, ill-tempered, sour-pussed shopkeeper. She has dark skin and icy, piercing blue eyes. Wears standard work clothing with a blaster on her left hip and a vibro-blade in her right boot. Despite appearances, she is commanding and elegant before her troops. Cold and formal with everyone except her husband, she never smiles. Fifteen years ago she commanded a company on garrison duty for the Sartran Corporation. When Sartran was disbanded by the Empire for treasonous activities, her mercenaries were imprisoned on trumped-up conspiracy charges. Released three years ago thanks to her husband's efforts, she discovered most of her command had died in prison and joined the Rebellion. Her only flaw is a too-great willingness to take risks — she wants revenge against the Empire.",
    source: "WEG40108 Classic Campaigns p.15"
