    equipment: "Comlink, datapad, hold-out blaster (3D), 2,500 credits",
    capsule: "A grizzled old Rodian who runs Tulagn's Starship Outfitters in the labyrinthine Wroona Starport. His legitimate business is moderately successful, though he supports it by dealing in stolen merchandise and contraband. The storefront is packed with shelves of spacer supplies, with tough-looking guards at the main door. His 'back room' for illegal dealings is only reachable through a maze-like series of dark alleys — nobody knows how he gets from the main shop to it. To make contact for shady deals, browse the Outfitters until you find a worthless trinket (Wontan sand glasses, Gamorrean amulets, supposed Alderaan rocks), try to buy it, and when told it's the last one, ask for more — he gives you a time to come to the back door. Gets stolen merchandise from landing bay workers who misdirect crates his way. Most loyal to his local Wroonian connections over transient smugglers.",
    source: "WEG40141 Platt's Smugglers Guide p.67-68"
