    capsule: "One of the major information brokers in Lan Barell's Shulell City. He has a surprisingly well-appointed apartment in the Grill, the city's bustling black market district and haven for refugees and offworld elements. Nestled among precious ferns, palms, and potted crawler vines, Phontos maintains a serene atmosphere to coordinate his information-gathering business. He rarely leaves his tropical office — contacts and customers come to him, resulting in a steady stream of visitors each day. Phontos scrutinizes those knocking at his door and does not deal with anyone too scruffy-looking. He keeps a hold-out blaster handy and probably has a secret escape route hidden among the creeper vines covering his walls. Few know why he's hiding on a system three days past the Outer Rim terminus of the Enarc Run — some suspect Imperial trouble, and crime lord enforcers occasionally come looking for him.",
    source: "WEG40141 Platt's Smugglers Guide p.72-73"
