    capsule: "Charger's Irregulars specialize in brushfire wars and hot spots where a small but effective infantry force can do some damage. The unit wanders the Outer Rim looking for work, consisting of about 15 soldiers-for-hire with specialized skills and combat experience. Major Charger is a grizzled veteran — a highly-wound, uncompromising combat commander on the battlefield, and a soft-spoken, polite gentleman when making business arrangements. The years and battles have worn him into a quiet, contemplative veteran out of the war zone and an unfeeling fighting machine in combat. Charger realizes the benefit of contacts and favors — the Irregulars get by as much by accepting handouts and good will as by their firepower. They don't mind pulling docking bay patrol duty for spacers or moving crates, and are enthusiastic when favors involve blasting enemies.",
