    move: 11,
    equipment: "Bow with arrows (2D+2), water skin, osma bag and ointments, provisions for one week",
    capsule: "Ibhaan'l shamen run the Uhl Dooba'l ('the peaceful place'), an immaculately maintained outbuilding shrine on the edge of Vakeyya, believed to be over two millennia old. They are experienced desert guides who welcome conversation with outsiders, eager to learn about the value systems of foreign beings. For a donation, a shaman will thoughtfully assemble an osma bag — a small leather pouch containing a pinch of blessed Socorran sand and personal trinkets chosen after speaking at length with the recipient. The shaman pieces together a life-destiny path from the chosen relics. Items may come from the shaman's own collection or be gathered on a journey of several days. Socorrans are avid storytellers; asking about a Socorran's osma is a sure way to win their friendship.",
    source: "WEG40154 Black Sands of Socorro p.28"
