    capsule: "The younger and more inexperienced of the Chabak cousins, Padda likes to 'talk the big talk.' He often brags about his gambling and romantic conquests beyond the Anchor, trying to impress potential gambling colleagues and love interests. In truth, Padda has had little experience away from the Twi'lek homeworld and does not seem to realize how close he actually comes to getting his head-tails blasted off by some irate customer. Padda's parents are quite powerful on the Twi'lek homeworld — they would immediately blame Quink if something should happen to their son, and continually remind the older Twi'lek of his obligation to look after Padda.",
