    equipment: "Flamestriker armor (+1D energy, +2D physical, -1D Dexterity and related skills; internal targeting sensors add +2 to hit with ranged weapons), sniper blaster (5D)",
    capsule: "Before Palpatine's rise to power, Norjax Thall and the Flamestrike Legion defended the Bamula sector from foreign insurrection. Small and cohesive, the Legion was well-trained and equipped, reputed to be invincible — until they met their match against the expanding Galactic Empire and were forcibly disbanded. Staying ahead of the Imperial tide, Norjax sought employment with various mercenary organizations, being orbitally inserted into hot landing zones on backwater worlds where his ill-equipped opponents were easily dispatched. The anarchy of these primitive national wars eventually drove him to seek work closer to the Core. He signed on with New Cov Biomolecule Company's security force before leaving to become involved in organized crime's 'civilized' warfare. During an assignment to neutralize a Syndicate One operation, the opposing crime lords settled their differences before further conflict — and Saujutta was so impressed by Norjax's command and control abilities that she insisted he be put on her permanent payroll. Since then he has served as weapons and tactical expert for Saujutta's business ventures. He is a tall, grizzled, pepper-haired Human with cold eyes, who proudly wears his battered mustard-yellow Flamestriker armor.",
