    equipment: "Comlink, heavy blaster pistol (5D), knife (STR+1D)",
    capsule: "Like most of his kind, Vex is a mysterious Defel motivated by his own unrevealed goals. Greezim Trentacal first heard of him when his name was mentioned with some regard by one of Trentacal's slave buyers. When introduced, Vex was initially uninterested in becoming Trentacal's personal bodyguard — the Defel had other matters requiring his attention and little time for what he saw as a petty and slovenly slave lord. But Vex quickly changed his mind when he found himself trapped between rivals to Trentacal's local interests and the firepower of the Karazak Slavers Guild that came to protect Trentacal. The Defel decided joining Trentacal's slaving operations was perhaps the best way to accomplish his own mysterious goals, and has served faithfully ever since for reasons he keeps to himself. Trentacal has informally elevated him to personal lieutenant in charge of the more mundane aspects of the slaving operation. Vex's invisibility-cloaking fur lets him stalk the dark corners of Atron's Mistress unseen — vulnerable only to bright light. He was killed on Gabredor III when Sully Tigereye flooded Trentacal's stateroom with full glow-sphere lighting and finished him with a vibro-axe.",
