    move: "10",
    equipment: "Comlink, datapad, personal data journal",
    capsule: "Doctor Maxina Sensis is an eager, attentive young xenoarchaeologist and exploratory historian currently attached to the Scout Service's Daxis Outpost in the Jandolhoon system. Her bright, optimistic outlook and passion for detail have earned her the position of Chief Researcher of the Daxis Outpost and the sincere respect of Korren Starchaser, who considers her the authority on analyzing and cataloging the artifacts that make their way back to known space through his team's hands. Originally from the Parkis system, Maxina's lifelong goal was to make important new discoveries well before anyone else had even thought of them. She was on the fast track to a comfortable Corporate Sector research job when she saw a Scout Service promotional holo just days before graduation — three hours after receiving her honors credits she was on a shuttle to the Daxis Outpost. Some colleagues are mystified by her desire to remain 'in the field' instead of taking a safer, higher-paying post closer to the Core, but Maxina knows she's found her niche when she gets her hands on new data or an exotic artifact weeks ahead of everyone else in the Service. She is currently hard at work trying to decipher the strange sculptures Korren's team brought back from the Serianan Belt, and is searching for another scouting team to do a more detailed system survey to confirm her theories about the artifacts and the markings on the asteroids of the belt.",
