    capsule: "Dirk Harkness leads the Black Curs, a small disaffected band of outlaws and smugglers bent on personal vengeance against the Empire. The Black Curs work loosely with the New Republic, conducting reconnaissance missions through Imperial-controlled space and feeding tactical reports to General Airen Cracken's intelligence network. Stubborn, impatient, and fiercely independent, Dirk struck out alone across Moorja's plains during a hot extraction to recover a Y-wing fighter the Black Curs had hidden in the Crumbling Lands — splitting from his teammates Platt Okeefe, Tru'eb Cholakk, and Jai Raventhorn rather than wait for a coordinated escape. He carries the only datapad copy of the Black Curs' Core Worlds reconnaissance report, hunted across the galaxy by Imperial Advisor Bregius Golthan and the warlord Moff Prentioch. After the New Republic refused to mount a rescue when Platt Okeefe was later captured, Dirk personally recruited mercenaries to break her out of Golthan's fortress on Voktunma — by which time the New Republic had officially declared the Black Curs outlaws. Full stats appear in Star Wars Adventure Journal #1 p.281.",
